===<span style="color:black;"><center>level 502 is the 503<sup>rd</sup> documented level of [[Backrooms Wiki|'''the backrooms.''']]</center></span>===

[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
[[File:Flexthosethighs.gif|link=|center|300px]]
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
<span style="color:black;">level 502 is an eternally expanding plane of pulsating human flesh, blood, tissue, and corpses all stacked atop one another. hundreds of thousands of  hands reach out beneath the layer of flesh, some of them reduced partially to bone, rapidly twisting and convulsing in ways no hand is capable of doing so. level 502's sky is a deep blood red, with clouds of thick black smoke. thousands of black tendrils reach upward, shaking and shifting in a rythmic and uniform manner. the level is strangely bright, with constant illumination from an unknown light source. the severe brightness of level 502 means that everything is in a state of high contrast, with bright white and red and jet 
black shadows.</span>

<span style="color:black;">the topology of the level shifts and fluctuates rapidly and drastically, ranging from small hills and lumps to gigantic mountains and cliffs, reported to be taller than any similar terrain in [[The Frontrooms|'''the frontrooms.''']] 
despite this drastic oscillation, the human appendages composing the level's plane remain structurally sound in place. it is currently unknown how this is possible, as normally something similar to this would collapse with a slight push or under it's own weight.</span>
[[File:Bellphotowitharmenian.png|link=|right|300px]]
<span style="color:black;">scattered about the level are a possibly infinite number of church bells, situated atop beams of moldy wood shrouded in pulsing veins, aligned in a perfect array and equally spaced from each other. the bells near constantly 
ring, a low sound similar to striking the lowest note on a standard piano, pausing every hour for approximately 25 minutes. the ringing has been said to inflict numerous psychological effects on wanderers, such as mental breakdowns and suicidal desire, as well as an urge to approach closer towards the nearest bell, and simply stare at it</span>

<span style="color:black;">alongside the ringing of the bells, the strangled breathing of exposed lungs and beating hearts are intensified by an order of magnitude, and muffled shrieks and cries from beneath the layer of flesh can eternally be heard, combining to a "maddening cacophony of human bodily function and eternal screaming", according to wanderers. though despite this intense ambience, the bell's ringing overpowers all the other noises somehow.</span>

<span style="color:black;">the bell's anomalous property of luring wanderers closer is the main cuase of death in level 502, as wanderers usually stay in the same spot until they either die of hunger, dehydration, or lack of sleep.</span>

<span style="color:black;">very rarely in the level, structures could appear, but so far the only documented structures found in level 502 have been old sheds, consisting of bloodied tools, old concrete floors, and pulsing veins surrounding the structure 
itself as well as the perimeter. these structures are unsafe to enter by unknown means.</span>
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
[[File:Thetractœæa.gif|link=|center|300px]]
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
<span style="color:black;">upon digging beneath the initial layers of corpses and flesh, one will penetrate into a lower layer of level 502, colloquially known as "the tract."</span>
[[File:Insidethetract.png|link=|right|300px]]
<span style="color:black;">the tract appears as a maze-like structure of tunnels reminiscent of a 
large intestine from the inside, coated in a thin layer of a substance similar in viscosity to mucus. the tract is almost 
labyrinthine in nature, with winding corridors and tunnels intersecting with each other in odd ways. much like the 
top layer, the tract rythmically pulsates in sync with the flesh above.</span>

<span style="color:black;">the layout of the tract is seemingly random, with no uniform shapes and twists. some 
areas of the level are hard to wander through, while other areas are unable to be explored. the only factor that stays constant within the tract is that any tunnel within the tract's labrynthine complex always connects to 
another, with no abrupt stops of dead ends.</span>

<span style="color:black;">unlike the top layer of the level, the tract remains eternally shrouded in darkness, with no light penetrating it.the only way to navigate through the tract is via bringing a light source, such as a 
flashlight. abnormally, any light source brought within the tract will be significantly darker than how it was on 
the top layer.</span>

<span style="color:black;">occasionally, purplish-black growths appear on the tract's walls, which are believed to 
be large tumors, and when punctured, release a thick black substance similar in many ways to tar. black veins also pulse on the level's ceiling, walls or floor occasionally, pumping presumably the same substance within the tumors.</span>
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
[[File:Thepsychiatricfacility.gif|link=|center|300px]]
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
<span style="color:black;">at the approximate center of the level lies a gigantic structure, known as "the psyche".</span>

<span style="color:black;">the psyche is a gigantic human heart, rising upward 15 feet in height. it's outer areas are surrounded by a thick pale white substance, which is slightly tacky, resemblent of animal fat.
hundreds of black veins branch out from the psyche like roots, branching deep into level 502's ground with some passing through the tract. the black veins nearest the psyche quiver and shake rather than pulse, and it intensifies the closer said veins are towards the psyche. any noise in the level gradually fades out the closer one is to the psyche, until the only thing that can be heard is the psyche beating.</span>

<span style="color:black;">very little to nothing is known about the psyche's purpose, or what it's capable of, but it could possibly be the reason level 502 exists, or was created along with the level.</span>

<span style="color:black;">the closer one approaches to the psyche, the further their brain will be filled with divine knowledge until they suddenly cease all brain function. it is currently unknown how the brain just stops functioning like this.</span> 
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
[[File:Entitynut.gif|link=|center|300px]]
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
<span style="color:black;">according to wanderer consensus, level 502 did in fact have entities prior to it's documentation, though all of them died due to the cognitive manipulation and mind control. wanderers stated that they observed entities standing near a ringing bell, and a few corpses could be seen.</span>

<span style="color:black;">as of the current day, level 502 lacks any direct threats, other than starvation and dehydration.</span>
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
[[File:Noravaleissohot.gif|link=|center|300px]]
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
<span style="color:black;">the death process in the level is different from most levels within the backrooms, as upon death, one will collapse to the ground rather stiffly, before black veins surround the body. the veins then drag the deceased body downward into the flesh, adding an additional corpse to the thousands.</span>

<span style="color:black;">it appears once one dies, the body is immediately revived, though they lose most of their human cognitive function.</span>

<span style="color:black;">it is currently unknown what happens after this.</span>
[[File:Separator.gif|link=|center|500px]]
<span style="color:black;">there is no entrances nor exits section, as it is currently unknown how to enter or exit this level, as there is no concrete evidence of any.</span>
